used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to the owner.\",\"kind\":\"dev\",\"methods\":{\"constructor\":{\"details\":\"Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.\"},\"owner()\":{\"details\":\"Returns the address of the current owner.\"},\"renounceOwnership()\":{\"details\":\"Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.\"},\"transferOwnership(address)\":{\"details\":\"Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.\"}},\"version\":1},\"userdoc\":{\"kind\":\"user\",\"methods\":{},\"version\":1}},\"settings\":{\"compilationTarget\":{\"Ownable.sol\":\"Ownable\"},\"evmVersion\":\"osaka\",\"libraries\":{},\"metadata\":{\"appendCBOR\":false,\"bytecodeHash\":\"ipfs\"},\"optimizer\":{\"enabled\":true,\"runs\":200},\"remappings\":[],\"viaIR\":true},\"sources\":{\"Ownable.sol\":{\"keccak256\":\"0x895bf42bad64fb8d689e338b83bcf63f8b5f3dd9afa36a8fdf8f07566b2ded1b\",\"license\":\"MIT\",\"urls\":[\"bzz-raw://0b10d6193d62ec254724f4f3dda4ef279ebbb6e4c224331a82ac1e031e2abaf5\",\"dweb:/ipfs/Qmc8rFfDKcGnkg87TW8r7kxCdd8okL57ZQ9qHCbGY64wAg\"]}},\"version\":1}"}},"TokenTimelock.sol":{"CloneFactory":{"evm":{"bytecode":{"functionDebugData":{},"generatedSources":[],"linkReferences":{},"object":"608080604052346014575b6003908160198239f35b5f80fdfe5f80fd","opcodes":"PUSH1 0x80 DUP1 PUSH1 0x40 MSTORE CALLVALUE PUSH1 0x14 JUMPI JUMPDEST PUSH1 0x3 SWAP1 DUP2 PUSH1 0x19 DUP3 CODECOPY RETURN JUMPDEST PUSH0 DUP1 REVERT INVALID PUSH0 DUP1 REVERT ","sourceMap":"4489:469:4:-:0;;;;;;;-1:-1:-1;4489:469:4;;;;;;;;;;"},"deployedBytecode":{"functionDebugData":{},"generatedSources":[],"immutableReferences"